therefore be the extent of women\u2019s participation in waged employment outside the agricultural sector \u2013 which tends to be in the urban areas and outside patriarchal controls. Figure I.22 shows this for a selection of countries \u2013 highlighting a relatively small proportion in a number of South Asian countries with the notable exception of Sri Lanka. Encouragingly, however, overall the proportion seems to be rising: among the countries reporting data, the average rose from 28.8 to 31.1 per cent. Only four countries reported falls. Figure I.22.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "904bfaaf-74bb-4e7a-8045-5fc157b445cd": {"__data__": {"id_": "904bfaaf-74bb-4e7a-8045-5fc157b445cd", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/future-within-reach", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "A Future within Reach", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/future-within-reach", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "1117b34cf39f853661cc30b53bc047e3df017276ff94ea9a33a6586257c782db"}, "2": {"node_id": "9f6875d1-58af-488b-90d3-bfdd9ee0da12", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/future-within-reach", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "1d216b42c0ec9ebb4f2d3d950cdef30bd85c313d2283450b60b56ac92be7f7b7"}}, "hash": "66513aea6b33800f71fdc29f8547295c3168f080d4ad75669615c2bb23509267", "text": "Only four countrie