, the region\u2019s picture of sty- mied progress is a reflection of compound- ing factors\u2014pollution, overexploitation of ground water, dilapidated systems, and in- sufficient levels of investment. The fail- ure to even come remotely close to achieving Target 10 weakens the Pacific\u2019s defense against overall poverty. South and Southwest Asia With baseline data: BANGLADESH \u2022 INDIA \u2022 IRAN, ISLAMIC REPUBLIC OF \u2022 MALDIVES \u2022 NEPAL \u2022 PAKISTAN \u2022 SRI LANKA Without baseline data: AFGHANISTAN \u2022 BHUTAN \u2022 TURKEY South and Southwest Asia is the most populous subregion.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "7c313273-d265-4590-9fbb-e2d9aa0f650d": {"__data__": {"id_": "7c313273-d265-4590-9fbb-e2d9aa0f650d", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-water-watch-2015", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia Water Watch 2015", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-water-watch-2015", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "7ca169e36099646df43de6f3ae3b4f986a6f6c20afde6a5ad3506928d1e573b7"}, "2": {"node_id": "54e39326-3fe8-43b6-b9d9-37dfd955c911", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-water-watch-2015", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "8aa6872bd141338a9f07581d8064ce5a9236dd4e52bcc52536c87337dda4b2c3"}}, "hash": "f15f541f0444eb5ed1eb61e5132acbfe79324