 Content/Guidelines, such as Programming and Implementation Arrangements. The RCB-MPT has assumed a lead role in supporting UN Reform simplification and harmonisation initiatives, in particular in serving as 48 RBAP focal point for the UNDG initiative \u201cHarmonised Arrangements for Cash Transfer to Implementing Partners (HACT)\u201d. In November 2005, with the arrival of the MPT leader, efforts resumed to form a full MPT at the RCB. Missions: Programme Development/Technical Backstopping/Policy Advice Country Practice / Service Line \u2013 Purpose Dates Specialist(s) 1. Sri Lanka, Maldives Indonesia CO Management Support, Capacity Assessment & Training Missions (Procurement Only) Q1 Yuri Afanasiev, Anthony Wood, Naoto Yamamoto (Sri Lanka), Jakob Agersnap, Volker Welter (Only Procurement) 2. China Review of Regional Project and CICETE Q1 Yuri Afanasiev 3. Myanmar Facilitators of the Management as a Function Practice Sub-regional Workshop for 5 COs Q1 Anthony Wood Tetsuo Kondo 4. Samoa, Fiji (PRSC) Multi-functional Integrated Project Management Capacity Building Missions Organised to Samoa and Fiji Relying on Toolkit for Managing Q2 Anthony Wood, M. S. Tinauli, Volker Welter 5. Bhutan Project Management of Atlas Q3 Anthony Wood M. S. Tinauli 6. Indonesia Resource Mobilisation and Partnership Building Jointly with South-South Cooperation for Tsunami Q3 Tetsuo Kondo 7. Lao PDR Resource Mobilisation and Partnership Building, focused on Lao UXO Q3 Tetsuo Kondo 8. Sri Lanka Resource Mobilisation and Partnership Building Jointly with South-South Cooperation for Tsunami Q3 Tetsuo Kondo 9. Maldives Resource Mobilisation and Partnership Building Jointly with South-South Cooperation for Tsunami Q3 Tetsuo Kondo 10. Sri Lanka (RCC) Policy Advice, Capacity Assessment and Recommendations Notes concerning RCC shift to DEX Q4 Anthony Wood 11. Pakistan Policy Advice on Emergency Relief Cash Management and Field Banking Policies and Procedures and on DEX implementation involving UNV 