and around similar knowledge activities to stimulate real-time exchange of experiences and knowledge and the creation of mutually beneficial communities of practices; and, \u2022 Practice presentations at the cluster meetings were reinforced by products and good practices displayed at the fair. The Knowledge Services Team tailored a one day partnership building and knowledge management workshop for 40 UNESCAP officials to demonstrate UNDP\u2019s knowledge management experience and to facilitate UNESCAP\u2019s own knowledge management strategy. The team also designed and facilitated a three-day sub-Regional Competency building Training Workshop in Hanoi for 20 national staff from Lao PDR, Myanmar, Cambodia and Vietnam in the areas of building and sharing knowledge and learning; UN core values; team building; and, task management. The team has been involved in supporting Knowledge Fairs in the Pacific (Samoa, Papua New Guinea and Fiji), and recently participated in and presented UNDP\u2019s network experience at the annual Knowledge Management Asia 2005 conference. Furthermore, the team co-negotiated and attended an inter-regional workshop on Global KM Framework (Bangkok, Beirut, Bratislava, Colombo, Johannesburg, Panama and Headquarters). Knowledge sharing for development One of UNDP\u2019s comparative advantages lies what we gain from experience. But the \u201cknowledge premium\u201d derives from sharing it. The RCB\u2019s \u201cregional advantage\u201d allows us to translate country level experience into policy advice for use elsewhere, and it helps us to turn policy advice into options and programmes in countries and regionally. In April, the first ever UNDP-internal Knowledge Fair was organised with RR/DRRs from the 25 Asia-Pacific COs. In addition to a wide display of publications and other resources, 57 country-level \u201cgood practices\u201d were were bought and sold in a people-to-people marketplace game. Awards were given to the best sellers as well as for best impact, ease of replication and best packaging. Results \u2013 Countries and colleagues were connected, and learned from each other. RR/DRRs put their \u201cresource mobilisation\u201d skills to the test. A number of the shared good practices are being replicated elsewhere.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "c058627a-9c6d-4928-837c-43991c66b17f": {"__data__": {"id_": "c058627a-9c6d-4928-837c-43991c66b17f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/undp-regional-centre-bangkok-annual-report-2005", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "UNDP Regional Centre in Bangkok Annual Report 2005", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/undp-regional-centre-bangkok-annual-report-2005", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "d42e38acd1e13aa758caa45bc94684f0f121d3fa4900a725a7c06e37c0cebb9c"}, "2": {"node_id": "0a9d9a7e-54d4-48d8-86a7-fde4859494ff", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/undp-regional-centre-bangkok-annual-report-2005", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "6e6184dee4eb0fdada6531806c2c6464ff74feba0b5327f8e1a8e3af51af3937"}}, "hash": "bcfc357c4bd9c1e84155d8130757beeeaa8ca5ae5bee2943879b3527b2360843", "text": "A number of the shared good practices are being replicated elsewhere. The Fair proved itself as a demonstration project on the value of Knowledge Fair, with discussions on county level k